JOHANNESBURG – The Standard Bank Purchasing Manager’s Index (PMI) shows that business activities are still under strain in South Africa. Last month the PMI showed shrinking production levels and a drop in new orders. It has gained just over a percentage point, rising to 49,6%. Anything below 50-points shows a contraction in business conditions. READ: South Africa's private-sector activity little changed in May, PMI shows The bank says it reveals a weak economy, struggling to cope with depressed business and consumer confidence. It further indicated that the bleak fiscal and economic outlook reflected in the Finance Minister’s medium-term budget policy statement means the trend is likely to continue. eNCA